<?xml-stylesheet type="text/xsl" href="mathml.xsl"?><html xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml" xmlns:pref="http://www.w3.org/2002/Math/preference" pref:renderer="mathplayer-dl"><head><meta http-equiv="Content-Type" content="text/html; charset=UTF-8" /><title>glResetMinmax</title><meta name="generator" content="DocBook XSL Stylesheets V1.69.1" /></head><body><div class="refentry" lang="en" xml:lang="en"><a id="glResetMinmax"></a><div class="titlepage"></div><div class="refnamediv"><h2>Name</h2><p>glResetMinmax — reset minmax table entries to initial values</p></div><div class="refsynopsisdiv"><h2>C Specification</h2><div class="funcsynopsis"><p><code class="funcdef"> void <b class="fsfunc">glResetMinmax</b>(</code><var class="pdparam">target</var><code>)</code>;<br /> GLenum <var class="pdparam">target</var>;</p></div></div><div class="refsect1" lang="en" xml:lang="en"><a id="id4781963"></a><h2>Parameters</h2><div class="variablelist"><dl><dt><span class="term"><em class="parameter"><code>target</code></em></span></dt><dd><p>
                    Must be
                    <code class="constant">GL_MINMAX</code>.
                </p></dd></dl></div></div><div class="refsect1" lang="en" xml:lang="en"><a id="id4781855"></a><h2>Description</h2><p>
            <code class="function">glResetMinmax</code> resets the elements of the current minmax table to their
            initial values: the ``maximum'' element receives the minimum possible
            component values, and the ``minimum'' element receives the maximum
            possible component values.
        </p></div><div class="refsect1" lang="en" xml:lang="en"><a id="id4781874"></a><h2>Notes</h2><p>
            <code class="function">glResetMinmax</code> is present only if <code class="code">ARB_imaging</code> is returned when <span class="citerefentry"><span class="refentrytitle">glGetString</span></span>
            is called with an argument of <code class="constant">GL_EXTENSIONS</code>.
        </p></div><div class="refsect1" lang="en" xml:lang="en"><a id="id4781900"></a><h2>Errors</h2><p>
            <code class="constant">GL_INVALID_ENUM</code> is generated if <em class="parameter"><code>target</code></em> is not <code class="constant">GL_MINMAX</code>.
        </p><p>
            <code class="constant">GL_INVALID_OPERATION</code> is generated if <code class="function">glResetMinmax</code> is executed
            between the execution of <span class="citerefentry"><span class="refentrytitle">glBegin</span></span> and the corresponding
            execution of <span class="citerefentry"><span class="refentrytitle">glEnd</span></span>.
        </p></div><div class="refsect1" lang="en" xml:lang="en"><a id="id4768489"></a><h2>See Also</h2><p>
            <span class="citerefentry"><span class="refentrytitle">glMinmax</span></span>
